replies.msg: My friend Pete has been having a crush on this girl named Jo who he met via CMB for many years but Jo has a boyfriend. His friend said "that's totally fair. She's quite attractive" But hee beginning to realise he has no place in her scheme of things. He's just being a door mat so I told him to forget her. She's just not worth it. His dad said "you'll be better off without her" His uncle said top "you would be better off without her" Pete works as an accounting manager at hilton but if he takes the job in big 4 he'll be five thousand dollars a month better off but he's still better off now than he was two years ago when he was working beneath everyone else in the department. He thinks a junior accountant position is beneath him. If he hadn't taken the CPA exam he wouldn't be working as a manager now. He's a science fiction fan. he said "if scientists would invent a starship I would quit my job and spend the rest of my life roaming the universe" His sister recently married her childhood sweetheart. Her mother felt she was marrying beneath her though. Her uncle too feels her husband is beneath her. She enjoys socializing with the better off. Pete was away on a business trip to Hokkaido last month. After his trip I said "if you should travel there again can you get me a pack of white lover cookies please?" Hes a computer expert. His cousin has to write a report which is due on wednesday but she's having problems with her computer. If he would go and fix her computer she'll be so thankful for his help. She also has exams next Monday so she's better off revising at home over the weekend. Pete is a kickboxing fan. His favourite fighter Dan recently won his retirement fight. He's eternally grateful to his coaches and thankful that he got a job as a colour commentator after he retired from the sport. All thr fans want to see randy versus Fred. If Fred will sign a deal with the company Dana will make the fight happen. When randy was reading the terms and conditions of the contract dana's assistant said "if you would just sign here please" Pete's brother is a concierge in a hotel. I did "if it'll make you feel happy I'll come to stay for a night as company for you while your colleagues are away" He threw a party last week. His television is cheap and nasty. As some of us wanted to watch the news I said "if I could turn the television on" He then said "sure. if you would switch to the news channel" I saw joey live twice. The first time I saw her concert witg my friends we were late. I remember I said "look at the time. The concert will have begun" It was quarter to nine. The concert would've started by then.
